snippet.textDisplay:
This song for me is a lot about the contrast the concept has been able to make. Right from the starting music which hardly gives any idea of fusing rock and QBs impact with sammi's folklore. Umair definitely puts his voice well building it up with the awesome drummer and violinists. The base guy is always on his toes and its lovely to hear the notes at places. Did you notice the flute all this time. So amazing! 
Did you hear the dholak and drum working besides. I am sure you also noticed the paino moving all the time like base and that guy on the mandolin (if I am not wrong) and the repeating rhythm they all make together to back up QB perfectly. 
Ofcourse the chorus are there unnoticed as ever. Some special moments are definitely with the drummer in the end taking an alternate route and merging again.. lovely.
Just listen to this track to notice the intricacies and am sure you will not get bored ever. 

Congratulations Team!
